Here's a simple web application that allows users to calculate their yearly sugar intake, view potential health risks, and get an estimate of how much money companies might be making from sugar sales based on that intake. The entire application is contained within a single HTML file with embedded CSS and JavaScript.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Sugar Intake Calculator</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
            color: #333;
        }
        h1, h2, h3 {
            color: #e74c3c;
        }
        input[type="number"] {
            width: 200px;
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background-color: #2ecc71;
            border: none;
            color: white;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        #result {
            margin-top: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #e74c3c;
            padding: 15px;
            background-color: #fff;
            display: none;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Sugar Intake Calculator</h1>
    <p>Enter your daily sugar intake in grams:</p>
    <input type="number" id="sugarIntake" placeholder="Daily Sugar Intake (g)" />
    <button onclick="calculate()">Calculate</button>

    <div id="result">
        <h2>Your Results:</h2>
        <p id="yearlyIntake"></p>
        <h3>Potential Risks:</h3>
        <ul id="risks"></ul>
        <h3>Estimated Company Revenue:</h3>
        <p id="revenue"></p>
    </div>

    <script>
        function calculate() {
            const sugarIntake = parseFloat(document.getElementById('sugarIntake').value);
            if (isNaN(sugarIntake) || sugarIntake < 0) {
                alert("Please enter a valid sugar intake amount.");
                return;
            }

            // Calculate yearly intake
            const yearlyIntake = sugarIntake * 365;
            document.getElementById('yearlyIntake').innerText = `You consume approximately ${yearlyIntake} grams of sugar per year.`;

            // Define health risks
            const risks = [
                "Obesity",
                "Type 2 Diabetes",
                "Heart Disease",
                "Tooth Decay",
                "Fatty Liver Disease",
                "Addiction",
            ];
            document.getElementById('risks').innerHTML = '';
            risks.forEach(risk => {
                const li = document.createElement('li');
                li.textContent = risk;
                document.getElementById('risks').appendChild(li);
            });

            // Estimate company revenue
            const averagePricePerGram = 0.005; // Price in dollars
            const totalRevenue = (yearlyIntake * averagePricePerGram).toFixed(2);
            document.getElementById('revenue').innerText = `Companies may make around $${totalRevenue} from your sugar consumption per year.`;

            // Show results
            document.getElementById('result').style.display = 'block';
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Instructions to Use:

1. Copy the entire code block into a new file and save it with an `.html` extension (e.g., `sugar_intake_calculator.html`).
2. Open the file in a web browser.
3. Enter your daily sugar intake in grams and click the "Calculate" button to see your yearly sugar intake, potential health risks, and estimated company revenue. 

### Features:
- Users can input their daily sugar intake.
- The app calculates yearly sugar intake.
- It lists potential health risks associated with high sugar consumption.
- It estimates how much revenue companies might make from consumers based on their sugar intake. 

Feel free to customize the design and the calculations further if necessary!

